  "doc_id": "10460",
  "text": "A cytolysin purified from the culture supernatant of an El Tor biotype strain, N86, had an apparent molecular mass of 60 to 65 kDa (mature HlyA) [CITATION_1] , although the predicted molecular size of the product of the cloned gene was around 82 kDa (prepro-HlyA) [CITATION_2] . We had previously detected a 79-kDa precursor form (pro-HlyA) in the supernatants of earlier cultivation stages by Western blotting (immunoblotting) and pulse-chase analysis [CITATION_3] . The results of sequencing the Nterminal amino acids of the 79-kDa pro-HlyA and the mature HlyA suggested that the 82-kDa prepro-HlyA is processed into 79-kDa pro-HlyA by release of the signal peptide of 25 amino acid residues and is then excreted into the supernatant through the outer membrane [CITATION_4] . The 79-kDa pro-HlyA has been found to be further processed into 65-kDa mature HlyA in culture supernatants following cleavage of the N-terminal 15-kDa polypeptide of the pro-HlyA (pro region). This cleaving process that turns pro-HlyA into mature HlyA is thought to occur via extracellular proteolysis, but the protease or proteases which are responsible have not been determined.",
